doc.after: The blue whale is the largest animal ever known to have lived.[33][34] By comparison, one of the largest known dinosaurs of the Mesozoic Era was Argentinosaurus,[35] which is estimated to have weighed up to 90 tonnes (99 short tons), comparable to the average of blue whale.[36] Amphicoelias fragillimus, at an estimated 122 tonnes (134 short tons) is still lighter than the largest blue whales, despite being 200 feet (61Â m) in length.[37]
